  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Pharmacokinetic concentrations in plasma will be measured at a central lab using a validated bioanalytical assay. Plasma samples will be drawn according to specific schedules for each drug</measure>
    <time_frame>24 hours</time_frame>
    <description>to determine the Pharmacokinetics of rifampin, ticarcillin-clavulanate, and clindamycin</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Safety review will be performed through monitoring of adverse events each day that the infant is on study</measure>
    <time_frame>7 days after last study dose</time_frame>
    <description>adverse events, serious adverse events, serious suspected adverse reactions, serious adverse reactions, suspected adverse reaction, adverse reactions will be assessed.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
